sql:
SELECT go_id, SUM(hits_in_term) AS total_hits
FROM go_terms
GROUP BY go_id;

SELECT go_id, COUNT(gene_orf_id) AS total_gene_orfs
  FROM genes_orf
  GROUP BY go_id;

external_knowledge:
GO terms refer to Gene Ontology terms, which are used to describe the function of genes and gene products; 
Fold enrichment is a measure used in the context of GO terms to describe how much more (or less) often a particular term is associated with a particular set of genes compared to the expected frequency; 
p-value is a raw measure indicating the probability of observing the given (or more extreme) fold enrichment by chance.

